								"description": "> Clooudability API Keys do not expire. As long as the user record is active in Cloudability, the attached API key can either be Enabled, Regenerated, or Disabled. \n  \n\nThis is the legacy authentication format. While it is still operational Cloudability customers are being pushed to the more secure Frontdoor Authentication. **CLDY API AUTH WILL BE DEPRICATED**\n\nFor this reason, it is important that your organization does not use this methodology when setting up mission critical automation.\n\n[Getting started with Cloudability API V3](https://help.apptio.com/en-us/cloudability/api/v3/getting_started_with_the_cloudability.htm)\n\n> Cloudability Keys can be created by follow this click path Cloudability > Profile > Manage Profile > Preferences > (Wait a Moment) > Cloudability API > Enable/Regenerate/Disable (See Snip) \n  \n\n<img src=\"https://content.pstmn.io/77d652f6-b08a-4bf1-b231-24b119d0fa53/aW1hZ2UucG5n\" alt=\"\" height=\"645\" width=\"1896\">"
