						}
					],
					"description": "002 [Frontdoor Authentication](https://help.apptio.com/en-us/frontdoor/admin-guide/api/overview-api-keys-faq.html) is the standard across all Apptio products and it follows a key pair/opentoken methodology. A public and private key is attached to either a User or Service Account record in Access Administration and these keys are used to call for an Open Token.\n\nThis OpenToken can then be paired with the Apptio Current Environment ID to make call on the Cloudability API v3 endpoints for a period of 30 minutes before needing to call a new opentoken.\n\nAPI keys can be set to have \"No Experation\" or a \"90 Day Experation\".\n\n### Steps to calling any Apptio Endpoint with Frontdoor Auth:\n\n1. **Create API keys against a user or service account in Access Administration and elect for No Experation or 90-day Experation.**\n    1. This key must be given a Cloudability Admin permission at minimum. Keys can not have a higher level permission than the Frontdoor record they are attached to.\n2. **Call on the frontdoor endpoint with the Public and secret key in body as seen below (1. Get OpenToken)**\n    1. This token will be valid for 30-minutes.\n3. **The last piece of information you will need is the apptio-current-environment id of your cloudability instance. This endpoint should only ever be called one time as the** [**Environment ID**](https://help.apptio.com/en-us/frontdoor/admin-guide/api/api-environment.html?Highlight=environment) **will never change.**\n4. **Add your current apptio-opentoken and apptio-current-environment ID in the headers of any subsequent calls to authenticate. After 30-minutes you will need to call for a new/valid token.**"
				}
			],
			"description": "The 000 Authentication section covers the two types of authentication that currently support Cloudability End Points. These two forms of authentivation include [Cloudability Authentication](https://help.apptio.com/en-us/cloudability/api/v3/getting_started_with_the_cloudability.htm) and [Frontdoor Authentication](https://help.apptio.com/en-us/frontdoor/admin-guide/api/overview-api-keys-faq.html).\n\n001 [Cloudability Authentication](https://help.apptio.com/en-us/cloudability/api/v3/getting_started_with_the_cloudability.htm) follows a bearer token or \"Skeleton key\" format in which a key is provided on a user basis. This key is then used in tandem with basic autheticaiton formats to interact with Cloudability v3 Endpoints. _**It is important to understand that this method of authentication is soon to be depricated in favor of the more secure Frontdoor Authentication method.**_\n\n002 [Frontdoor Authentication](https://help.apptio.com/en-us/frontdoor/admin-guide/api/overview-api-keys-faq.html) is the standard across all Apptio products and it follows a key pair/opentoken methodology. A public and private key is attached to either a User or Service Account record in Access Administration and these keys are used to call for an Open Token.\n\nThis OpenToken can then be paired with the Apptio Current Environment ID to make call on the Cloudability API v3 endpoints for a period of 30 minutes before needing to call a new opentoken.\n\nAPI keys can be set to have \"No Experation\" or a \"90 Day Experation\"."
